## ⚙️ Input Parameters (Actor Input Schema)

| Parameter | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `csvFile` | string | conditional | – | Uploaded CSV file (if using CSV). |
| `emails` | array | conditional | – | JSON array of email objects (if not using CSV). |
| `columnMapping` | object | no | `{}` | Maps placeholders to CSV column names. |
| `rejectionTemplate` | string | no | `""` | Template with placeholders to generate `originalEmail`. |
| `defaultTone` | string | no | `"warm and honest"` | Fallback tone when not specified per email. |
| `maxConcurrency` | integer | no | `5` | Number of parallel requests (1–20). |
| `timeout` | integer | no | `60` | Timeout in seconds per email. |

> **Note:** Either `csvFile` or `emails` must be provided.

---

## 📤 Output

SETI produces a **dataset** (Apify dataset) with the following fields:

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `originalEmail` | The input email (or generated from template). |
| `improvedEmail` | The rewritten, warmer version (or `null` if error). |
| `toneUsed` | The tone applied to this email. |
| `status` | `"success"` or `"error"`. |
| `timestamp` | ISO timestamp of processing. |
| `error` | Error message (if any). |

Users can export the dataset as **CSV or JSON**.

